11:31.224 --> 11:31.990
and moving his lips.            

11:33.426 --> 11:35.961
        I think he was countin''
         the bolts on the floor.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.096
No, come on.                    

11:37.163 --> 11:38.430
He wouldn't do that             
in the middle of a game.        

11:38.498 --> 11:39.231
    Hey, look, they're gonna    
        interview Kevin.        

11:39.299 --> 11:40.499
          Here's Glen.          

11:40.567 --> 11:42.568
      This is Glen Ordway       
  on the floor of the Garden.   

11:42.635 --> 11:44.737
        We're gonna see         
 if we can catch Kevin McHale,  

11:44.804 --> 11:46.138
 ask him a couple of questions  

11:46.206 --> 11:48.140
      and find out exactly      
        what went wrong         

11:48.208 --> 11:49.608
 out on the floor here tonight. 

11:49.676 --> 11:51.276
  Uh, here he comes right now.  

11:51.344 --> 11:53.679
    Uh, Kevin, can I ask you    
     a couple of questions?     

11:53.747 --> 11:55.447
Hundred and nine,               
hundred and ten,                

11:55.515 --> 11:57.216
hundred and eleven,             
hundred and twelve...           

11:57.317 --> 11:59.184
Now look what you've done!      

11:59.285 --> 12:01.220
      You have ruined him!      

12:01.287 --> 12:03.422
  You've ruined Kevin McHale!   

12:03.490 --> 12:04.923
                        You took
                     the scoring

12:04.991 --> 12:08.260
machine, one of Boston's        
greatest living sports legends  

12:08.328 --> 12:09.695
and turned him                  
into...                         

12:09.763 --> 12:12.698
          one of you!           

12:14.200 --> 12:18.804
        GUYS (chanting):        
 Kevin, Kevin, Kevin, Kevin...  

12:26.346 --> 12:28.714
         (phone rings)          

12:28.782 --> 12:30.749
Cheers.                         

12:30.817 --> 12:31.917
  Yeah, Sammy, this is Kevin.   

12:31.985 --> 12:33.485
          Hey, Kevin!           
    Hey, Kevin McHale.          

12:33.553 --> 12:34.987
            OTHERS:             
          Hey, Kevin!           

12:35.088 --> 12:37.489
                Hey, Sammy, boy,
    I'm having a rough night.   

12:37.557 --> 12:39.725
        Yeah, ooh, boy,         
      we caught the game.       

12:39.793 --> 12:41.794
  Yeah, you really stunk it up  
        out there, huh?         

12:41.861 --> 12:43.896
     Hey, I saw you pitch.      

12:43.963 --> 12:45.698
      You're not entitled       
         to an opinion.         

12:45.765 --> 12:48.300
      You know what it is,      
        though...               

12:48.368 --> 12:49.601
    it's those bolts.           

12:49.669 --> 12:51.303
  I tell you, I can't get them  
        out of my mind.         

12:51.371 --> 12:53.372
You know, I've called the people
         all over town,         

12:53.440 --> 12:54.940
 and no two people seem to have 
        the same answer.        

12:55.008 --> 12:56.975
 Sammy, it's driving me crazy.  

12:57.043 --> 12:58.911
 Kevin, you, you got to take it 
        easy with this.         

12:58.978 --> 13:00.846
     I mean, bar trivia can     
        eat you up, pal.        

13:00.914 --> 13:03.048
Kevin, it's not too late!       
        Get help!               

13:03.116 --> 13:04.149
Don't...                        

13:04.217 --> 13:05.918
Honey, who's that?              

13:05.985 --> 13:07.419
                Just the guys   
                 down at Cheers.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.922
(sighs)                         

13:18.431 --> 13:21.300
My motive, of course,           
was to please Frasier.          

13:21.368 --> 13:23.102
But this evening, after dinner, 

13:23.169 --> 13:26.472
      he laughed so hard,       
cappuccino ran out of his nose. 

13:28.541 --> 13:30.809
Rebecca, you're a friend.       

13:30.877 --> 13:34.947
Does this permanent make my hair
    look utterly ridiculous?    

13:35.015 --> 13:36.782
                 No, not at all.

13:36.850 --> 13:38.684
                I think it's    
            a delightful change.

13:38.752 --> 13:39.885
            So do I.            

13:39.953 --> 13:41.320
    Damn that Frasier!          

13:41.388 --> 13:44.590
    For a moment, he had me     
believing I was a laughingstock.

13:44.657 --> 13:46.392
Thank you.                      

13:46.459 --> 13:48.861
            Don't mention it.   
            What're friends for?

13:50.430 --> 13:51.730
                How can you just
                    stand there,

13:51.798 --> 13:54.933
          staring at that hairdo
    and not bust a gut laughing?

13:55.001 --> 13:57.903
(voice straining):              
No problem.                     

14:00.473 --> 14:02.174
         Hi, everybody!         

14:02.242 --> 14:03.409
          Hey, Kevin!           

14:03.510 --> 14:05.644
                        FRASIER:
                 How come you're
                not in bed, man?

14:05.712 --> 14:07.579
Oh, I couldn't sleep.           

14:07.647 --> 14:08.881
  You got a big game tomorrow.  

14:09.049 --> 14:10.416
         I don't care.          

14:11.885 --> 14:14.219
      All I care about are      
          those bolts.          

14:14.287 --> 14:16.522
So I ran out and got a set      
  of blueprints to the Garden.  

14:16.589 --> 14:19.024
 Find out how many bolts there  
  are in that floor right now.  

14:19.092 --> 14:21.460
 Wait a minute. Where'd you get 
 blueprints this time of night? 

14:21.561 --> 14:23.062
Ah, I know somebody             
down at City Hall.              

14:23.129 --> 14:25.464
         Kind of a sports legend
              in this town, huh?

14:25.532 --> 14:26.732
Oh, yeah?                       
Yeah, all right.                

14:26.800 --> 14:28.734
            Oh, hey, gee, there,
            I'm sorry, Kevin,   

14:28.802 --> 14:30.102
                but these are   
                  the blueprints

14:30.170 --> 14:31.370
              for the new Garden
          that they're building.

14:31.438 --> 14:32.504
  No...                         
            Yeah, yeah, you see,

14:32.572 --> 14:35.607
                 there should be
          a mailbox right there.

14:35.675 --> 14:37.476
No, no.                         

14:37.577 --> 14:39.211
Oh, give me that phone!         
I hope the mayor's still up.    

14:39.279 --> 14:40.713
Give me that phone.             
                     No, no, no.

14:40.780 --> 14:42.881
  I don't think you should do   
that, man. Don't do that.       

14:42.949 --> 14:44.983
Sammy, I'm telling you          
right now, I got to know.       

14:45.051 --> 14:46.251
I got to know.                  
I'm telling you, nothing,       

14:46.319 --> 14:47.653
I mean nothing's                
going to stop me.               

14:47.754 --> 14:49.988
             Kevin.             

14:50.090 --> 14:52.691
    Good night, guys.           

14:55.228 --> 14:57.296
              You guys should be
          ashamed of yourselves.

14:57.364 --> 14:58.764
        You're like vampires.   

14:58.832 --> 15:02.434
                     Big-butted,
            do-nothing vampires.

15:02.502 --> 15:05.070
             And, and now you're
            trying to make Kevin
        one of your recruits.   

15:05.138 --> 15:06.605
                     Well, I say
            it's got to stop.   

15:06.673 --> 15:08.974
        I'm not going to let you
            screw up his career.

15:09.042 --> 15:10.509
Oh, come on,                    
lighten up, will you?           

15:10.577 --> 15:12.177
It's just Kevin's getting       
a little carried away           

15:12.245 --> 15:13.345
with bolts, that's all.         

15:13.446 --> 15:14.813
Yeah, sure, Sammy.              

15:14.914 --> 15:16.248
    Today it's how many bolts   
            are in the floor.   

15:16.316 --> 15:17.916
                Tomorrow they'll
                have him onto   

15:17.984 --> 15:19.885
             "If the Brady Bunch
        crashes in the Andes,   

15:19.953 --> 15:22.221
              who's going to eat
                     who first?"

15:24.424 --> 15:26.925
Well, they'd probably eat       
 the maid 'cause she ain't kin. 

15:29.963 --> 15:31.864
        Well, you know,         
  but if they're smart there,   

15:31.931 --> 15:34.833
they'll ask her first how       
she should best prepare herself.

15:34.901 --> 15:38.704
            Stop it!            

15:38.772 --> 15:39.838
All right,                      
so what do we do?               

15:39.906 --> 15:40.873
      Well, we'll go down       
         to the Garden          

15:40.940 --> 15:43.042
    and just count the bolts    
         in the floor,          

15:43.109 --> 15:45.244
  so we can settle this thing   
and get Kevin back on his game. 

15:45.311 --> 15:46.445
                      All right?

15:46.513 --> 15:47.513
          Well, how are we going
        to get in there, Sam?   

15:47.580 --> 15:48.747
                 Don't they lock
            the Garden at night?

15:48.815 --> 15:50.883
        Oh, hey, Woody, don't   
        worry about those locks.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.251
                 We can get past
                any one of them,

15:52.318 --> 15:53.552
                  with my trusty
            Swiss Army Knife.   

15:53.653 --> 15:55.220
          (chuckles):           
    Yeah, I got the big one     

15:55.288 --> 15:58.123
with the, uh,                   
tweezer-toothpick combo.        

15:58.191 --> 16:00.225
Yeah.                           
            That's a beauty,    
              Mr. Clavin.       

16:00.293 --> 16:01.660
      Yeah, thanks, Woody.      

16:01.728 --> 16:04.797
Yeah, every soldier in the Swiss
    Army owns one of these.     

16:04.864 --> 16:06.665
        That's why nobody messes
            with Switzerland.   

16:06.733 --> 16:09.902
Yeah, I'd rather run buck naked 
through the neighborhood        

16:09.969 --> 16:11.337
than be without this baby.      

16:11.404 --> 16:13.672
    Why is that always          
    the other option?           

16:20.747 --> 16:23.615
        (lights buzzing)        

16:23.750 --> 16:26.552
          Whoa, ho-ho!          

16:26.619 --> 16:27.519
                          WOODY:
                    Are they on?

16:27.587 --> 16:29.555
                    Uh, yeah!   

16:29.656 --> 16:31.557
    Look at this, huh?          

16:31.658 --> 16:33.258
         Boston Garden.         

16:33.326 --> 16:35.894
    I wake up this morning,     
thinking my life has no meaning,

16:35.995 --> 16:38.997
and now I'm standing here.      

16:39.065 --> 16:40.199
  Yeah, it really, really kind  
      of clears things up,      

16:40.266 --> 16:41.600
    doesn't it, Norm?           

16:41.668 --> 16:43.802
No, I'm still pretty sure       
    my life has no meaning,     

16:43.870 --> 16:46.138
     but I'm standing <i>here.</i>     

16:46.206 --> 16:47.439
(laughs)                        

16:47.507 --> 16:49.975
    Every part of this place    
    is special to me.           

16:50.043 --> 16:50.809
             Yeah.              

16:50.877 --> 16:52.678
                    It's sacred.

16:52.746 --> 16:54.747
        It's holy,              
  you know, like a cathedral.   

16:56.082 --> 16:57.516
    Think I'll rip a seat out   

16:57.617 --> 16:59.184
        and throw it in the back
                 of my car, huh?

16:59.252 --> 17:01.153
        Hey, wait a minute...   
What? What?                     

17:01.221 --> 17:02.121
          Forget that.          
What?                           

17:02.222 --> 17:04.289
        Hey, Mr. Clavin,        
    I have a question.          

17:04.357 --> 17:05.624
                      Yeah, fire
                     away there.

17:05.692 --> 17:08.093
Well, how can they play hockey  
in here-- there's no ice?       

17:08.194 --> 17:10.762
Oh, the ice is, uh, right       
 under the floor there, Woody.  

17:10.829 --> 17:12.364
It's under the floor right now? 

17:12.432 --> 17:13.365
          Absolutely!           

17:13.433 --> 17:14.566
         Why don't you, uh, pick

17:14.634 --> 17:16.468
             one of these things
            up, have a look-see?

17:16.536 --> 17:18.237
              Here, use my      
        Swiss Army Knife.       

17:18.304 --> 17:20.305
    Suppose anyone would mind   
         if we shot a few hoops?

17:20.373 --> 17:21.740
Hey, where'd you get that?      

17:21.808 --> 17:23.642
Out of the trunk of my car since
  last time I was at the gym.   

17:23.710 --> 17:25.010
Let's run the floor.            
                      All right!

17:25.178 --> 17:27.746
    Here we go! Here we go!     

17:29.249 --> 17:31.150
(chuckling):                    
When was the last time          
you were at the gym?            

17:31.217 --> 17:32.418
                I don't know.   

17:32.485 --> 17:33.619
            I used to go to that
        one next door to Cheers.

17:33.687 --> 17:35.354
         There's no gym         
      next door to Cheers.      

17:35.422 --> 17:36.288
                Yeah, there was.
              They tore it down.

17:36.356 --> 17:37.389
                     They put up
                 that bookstore.

17:37.457 --> 17:38.657
      There's no bookstore      
         there either.          

17:38.725 --> 17:40.726
         Oh, they tore that down
    and they put the bank there.

17:40.794 --> 17:42.261
The bank's been there           
as long as I can remember.      

17:42.328 --> 17:43.829
             Well, there you go.

17:44.464 --> 17:46.932
WOODY:                          
Wow!                            

17:47.000 --> 17:48.967
                 Well, what have
                        we here?

17:49.035 --> 17:50.703
Looks like plywood.             

17:50.770 --> 17:54.039
        Oh, great!              
    Hey, I can use the saw.     

17:54.107 --> 17:56.008
        (thumping)              

17:56.076 --> 17:57.943
                  Oh, great,    
              somebody's coming.

17:58.011 --> 17:59.545
                Woody, put, put,
             put the floor back.

17:59.612 --> 18:01.146
Come on, let's go.              

18:03.883 --> 18:05.951
          Woody, come on.       
             Hurry up.          

18:07.754 --> 18:09.088
          What a day.           

18:09.155 --> 18:11.790
      First Sammy gets me       
     Kevin McHale's jacket.     

18:11.858 --> 18:14.159
      Then I get to sneak       
    around the Garden.          

18:14.227 --> 18:16.595
    Even look at the plywood    
        under the floor.        

18:16.663 --> 18:18.731
  Now we're getting chased off  
      by security guards.       

18:18.798 --> 18:20.299
            (laughs)            

18:20.367 --> 18:21.967
        I'm sorry, guys.        

18:22.035 --> 18:24.536
I never had a more beautiful day
          in my life.           

18:29.109 --> 18:30.776
                 Drinking alone?

18:30.844 --> 18:34.847
No. Frasier asked to meet       
me to be here today.            

18:34.948 --> 18:37.316
    He probably wants a few     
      more boorish laughs       

18:37.384 --> 18:39.518
     at my hair's expense.      

18:39.586 --> 18:41.887
         Well, if it's          
    any consolation to you,     

18:41.955 --> 18:43.989
     I think that look does     
    something for you.          

18:44.057 --> 18:45.758
        Thank you.              

18:45.825 --> 18:47.426
    I didn't say what.          

18:51.398 --> 18:52.331
            Lilith?             

18:52.399 --> 18:55.367
Uh, please, don't speak.        

18:55.468 --> 18:57.836
I've behaved abominably.        

18:57.904 --> 19:00.572
You had the courage to try      
something different             

19:00.640 --> 19:02.107
in order to please me,          

19:02.175 --> 19:04.076
and I've repaid you             
with mockery,                   

19:04.144 --> 19:05.711
which is unforgivable.          

19:05.779 --> 19:09.648
But I, I hope you can           
forgive me because I love you.  

19:09.716 --> 19:11.250
And I love your hair.           

19:11.317 --> 19:14.486
And no matter how you might     
change your outer appearance,   

19:14.554 --> 19:19.058
you'll always be                
the most beautiful woman        
in the world to me.             

19:19.125 --> 19:20.392
                    Oh, Frasier!

19:30.737 --> 19:33.439
        Thanks, Rebecca.        

19:33.506 --> 19:35.174
Oh, I better keep one.          

19:37.077 --> 19:39.712
                        NORM:   
                There you go.   

19:39.779 --> 19:42.881
Yeah, McHale's playing          
a little better tonight, huh?   

19:42.949 --> 19:45.150
 Yeah, of course he is. As soon 
  as I told him how many bolts  

19:45.218 --> 19:46.385
were in the floor, he just      
  settled right into his game.  

19:46.453 --> 19:47.753
        Wait a minute. How could
              you tell him that?

19:47.821 --> 19:49.254
        We never had a chance   
                  to count them.

19:49.322 --> 19:52.558
 Well, I just made up a number, 
        you know.               

19:52.625 --> 19:54.426
I figure he'll never know       
        the difference.         

19:54.494 --> 19:56.795
As long as it improves his game,
you know, what's the harm?      

19:56.896 --> 19:58.397
             Right.             

19:58.465 --> 20:00.165
                          WOODY:
                     Sam, I have
                     a question.

20:00.233 --> 20:02.701
    Not now, Woody, I'm, uh,    
    watching the game here.     

20:02.769 --> 20:03.936
No, it's                        
really important.               

20:04.037 --> 20:05.637
             What?              

20:05.705 --> 20:08.107
Well, say a guy removed         
the bolts from a piece of floor 

20:08.174 --> 20:09.541
in a very                       
important building.             
                    Uh-huh.     

20:09.609 --> 20:12.644
Like, uh, I don't know,         
say, the Boston Garden.         

20:12.712 --> 20:14.013
And, and say a guard came,      

20:14.080 --> 20:17.649
and he didn't have time to put  
the bolts back in the floor.    

20:17.717 --> 20:19.284
What would happen?              

20:19.352 --> 20:21.954
        You didn't put the bolts
    back in the floor, Woody?   

20:22.022 --> 20:23.689
Oh, I knew                      
you'd catch that.               

20:23.757 --> 20:26.692
I should of just been           
honest with you, Sam.           

20:26.760 --> 20:28.660
What should I do?               

20:28.728 --> 20:31.163
  Oh, relax, will you, Woody?   
      For crying out loud,      

20:31.231 --> 20:32.965
 they got a crew there to check 
 on everything before the game. 

20:33.066 --> 20:34.533
        Yeah, I'm sure they just
         found the missing bolts

20:34.601 --> 20:36.001
              and replaced them.

20:36.102 --> 20:38.337
  I mean, even if they don't,   
I mean, what are the odds       

20:38.405 --> 20:40.639
 of somebody hitting that spot  
         exactly, huh?          

20:40.707 --> 20:42.741
         TV ANNOUNCER:          
     Bird passes to McHale.     

20:42.809 --> 20:44.476
      McHale is in for it,      
          stops short.          

20:44.544 --> 20:46.478
 Oh, he's tripped on something! 

20:46.579 --> 20:47.713
        He's down!              

20:47.781 --> 20:49.481
     It looks like a piece      
     of the floor came up.      

20:49.549 --> 20:52.551
 That hurt just looking at it!  

20:52.619 --> 20:54.887
Oh, no!                         

20:54.954 --> 20:56.522
I really did it                 
this time.                      

20:56.623 --> 20:58.824
No, no, no, no, no, no.         
Don't blame yourself, Woody.    

20:58.925 --> 20:59.825
         It's my fault.         

20:59.893 --> 21:01.527
      It was my birthday.       

21:01.594 --> 21:03.996
    I'm the one who got him     
  all interested in the bolts.  

21:04.064 --> 21:06.298
     No, no, it's me who dragged
                 us all out here

21:06.366 --> 21:08.033
            in the middle of the
        night to go count bolts.

21:08.101 --> 21:09.168
                It was my fault.

21:09.235 --> 21:10.302
  Oh, never would've happened   

21:10.370 --> 21:13.639
        if I didn't have        
      my Swiss Army Knife.      

21:13.707 --> 21:14.840
Guys, it was my fault.          

21:14.908 --> 21:16.709
I'm the one who took            
the bolts out of the floor.     

21:16.810 --> 21:19.011
     He's right, you know.      

21:19.112 --> 21:21.213
            That's true. Why are
                we being so hard
                on ourselves?   

21:21.281 --> 21:22.915
      Yeah, you heard him       
    admit that, didn't you?     

21:22.982 --> 21:24.817
    You guys, you heard it?     

21:34.961 --> 21:36.528
Hey, Kevin, how are you feeling?

21:36.596 --> 21:38.197
      Not too good, Woody.      

21:38.264 --> 21:39.264
          I don't know          
    what happened out there.    

21:39.332 --> 21:41.200
I must look like an idiot.      

21:41.267 --> 21:43.202
                It was my fault.

21:43.269 --> 21:44.870
  How could it be your fault?   

21:44.938 --> 21:47.239
         I'm the clown          
     that slipped and fell.     

21:47.340 --> 21:48.540
         You're right.          
        You were.               

21:48.608 --> 21:50.542
      You heard him, guys,      
     let's get out of here.     

21:50.610 --> 21:52.277
                 Listen, we have
                    a confession
                 to make, Kevin.

21:52.345 --> 21:53.512
                Uh, when we came

21:53.580 --> 21:55.647
    over here the other night   
             to count the bolts,

21:55.715 --> 21:57.249
                  we kind of got
                    carried away

21:57.317 --> 22:00.552
        and kind of took some of
    the bolts out and then...   

22:00.653 --> 22:03.722
            kind of forgot to   
            put them back in.   

22:03.790 --> 22:05.991
      You mean to tell me       
this really is your fault?      

22:06.059 --> 22:07.593
                  I'm afraid so.

22:07.660 --> 22:08.627
    Boy, that figures.          

22:08.695 --> 22:11.363
         With you guys,         
      that really figures.      

22:13.533 --> 22:14.733
 You know, I'll tell you what,  
            though,             

22:14.801 --> 22:16.201
      I guess I can't stay      
         too mad at you         

22:16.269 --> 22:18.404
'cause you finally solved       
 that bolt question, you know.  

22:18.471 --> 22:22.041
                  We got another
             confession to make.

22:22.108 --> 22:24.743
  We kind of never got around   
     to counting the bolts.     

22:24.844 --> 22:26.745
 Wait a minute. Wait a minute.  
     You trying to tell me,     

22:26.813 --> 22:28.247
  we still don't know how many  
 bolts there are in that floor? 

22:28.314 --> 22:30.249
            Yeah, but what is   
            the difference, man?
        You played a great game.

22:30.316 --> 22:31.850
         Yeah, but what         
     about tomorrow's game?     

22:34.187 --> 22:37.589
